Job description 6:

- As a Cybersecurity Analyst you will provide consulting support to the business units in implementing secure business solutions and responding to security incidents
You will test and aid in the implementation of appropriate detections, including documentation of incidents and playbooks
In addition, you will assist with configuring of safeguards at appropriate points in the Avery Dennison network
Specific areas of responsibility include, but are not limited to:

Incident Response

Perform incident response handling and management of forensic evidence, meeting SLAs and customer experience metrics
Respond to security incidents with top tier endpoint and cloud technologies
Create and maintain incident documentation and playbooks
Manage and monitor SIEM and other tools for suspicious system activity and handle investigations using proper forensic methodologies and regulations
Research
Participate in vendor advisory committees, threat intel organizations, and other industry
knowledge-sharing groups
Research emerging attacks and perform threat hunting activities
Security Tool Management

In partnership with cybersecurity engineers, evaluate new security technologies for integration with existing systems

Develop and maintain detection policies and alerts, including tuning for efficacy
Propose new uses for existing technologies to improve data quality and reduce risk
Perform tool evaluations and conduct proof of concepts
Manage alert ingest processes
Onboard new data sources into SIEM


Minimum Qualification:

Associate's degree in Computer Science, Information Technology or similar field, or equivalent experience
1+ years of information security related experience with a focus on endpoints, incident response, network, application, or architecture
Some familiarity with technology concepts across Windows, UNIX, database, network and web
Experience with EDR, SIEM, and cloud technologies
Passion and interest in security and understanding the latest threats
Strong interest and drive to identify/create and meet customers /business partners needs plus cultural empathy and team-player attitude to operate in complex multinational organization
Comfortable with multiple projects and able to manage a number of key tasks simultaneously
High degree of accuracy, good time-management and priority setting skills are important.
Ability to travel domestically and internationally up to 5%, as well as to work flexible hours
Preferred Qualifications:

Experience with regex, scripting, and/or API calls
Relevant security industry certifications, including but not limited to CompTIA Security+, CEH, CCNP, etc.
Experience in manufacturing or operational technology environments

