Roles & Responsibilities: - Develop and implement Cyber Threat Intelligence strategies to identify and mitigate potential cyber threats.- Design and implement Cybersecurity Strategy Development plans to safeguard information, infrastructures, applications, and business processes against cyber threats.
- Collaborate with cross-functional teams to ensure the security of enterprise systems, applications, data, assets, and people.
- Provide technical guidance and support to stakeholders on Cyber Threat Intelligence and Cybersecurity Strategy Development best practices.
Professional & Technical Skills: - 
Must To Have Skills: Expertise in Cyber Threat Intelligence and Cybersecurity Strategy Development.
- Good To Have Skills: Knowledge of security technologies such as firewalls, intrusion detection systems, and vulnerability scanners.
- Strong understanding of security frameworks such as NIST, ISO, and CIS.- Experience in conducting security assessments and audits.
- Excellent communication and interpersonal skills to effectively communicate technical findings to stakeholders. Additional Information: 
- The candidate should have a minimum of 4 years of experience in Cyber Threat Intelligence.
- The ideal candidate will possess a strong educational background in Computer Science, Information Technology, or a related field, along with a proven track record of delivering impactful data-driven solutions.- This position is based at our Bengaluru office.
