Job description 13:

- The Application Security Engineer in this role will be responsible for ensuring the security

and integrity of our applications and systems by implementing robust security measures,

conducting security assessments, and collaborating with cross-functional teams. This role

requires a strong technical background, deep knowledge of application security principles,

and the ability to identify and mitigate potential vulnerabilities.

Key Responsibilities

Perform Security Assessments: Conduct thorough security assessments of applications,

systems, and software components to identify vulnerabilities, security risks, and potential

weaknesses. Use industry-standard tools and methodologies to assess application security

posture.

Security Code Review: Conduct manual and/or automated code reviews to identify

application security flaws and vulnerabilities. Provide actionable recommendations and work

closely with development teams to implement necessary security improvements.

Secure Development Lifecycle (SDL): Collaborate with development teams to integrate

security practices & and privacy aspects into the software development lifecycle (security &

and privacy by design). Guide and assist in the adoption of secure coding practices, threat

modeling, and security testing methodologies.

Vulnerability Management: Manage the vulnerability identification and remediation

process. Track, prioritize, and communicate vulnerabilities to development teams and assist

in the implementation of appropriate mitigation strategies.

Security Testing: Conduct application security testing, including penetration testing,

vulnerability scanning, and security code analysis. Identify and validate security risks,

document findings, and collaborate with teams to resolve identified issues.

Security Standards and Policies: Stay updated with the latest application security

standards, best practices, and regulatory requirements. Develop and maintain security

policies, procedures, and guidelines related to application security.

Incident Response: Participate in incident response activities, investigating and

addressing security incidents related to applications or systems. Collaborate with the

incident response team to identify root causes and implement preventive measures.

Security Awareness and Training: Promote security awareness by providing training and

guidance to development teams and stakeholders. Raise awareness about common security

threats, secure coding practices, and emerging trends in application security.

Industry Best Practices: Engage in professional development activities, including

attending security conferences, participating in industry forums, staying informed about the

latest trends and advancements in application security, and promoting best practices within

the team.

Documentation and Reporting: Provide periodic updates and reporting on information security issues.Maintain up to date security policies and procedure documentation.Maintain and regularly update the

compliance tracker with relevant information.Ensure timely and accurate reporting of

security risks and periodic reports to management and relevant stakeholders / regulators.Role & responsibilities

