Job description 14:

-> Bachelor's degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, or a related field.

> 3+ years of experience in cyber security, with a focus on penetration testing and vulnerability assessment.

> Strong understanding of information security and network security principles.

> Experience with a variety of cyber security tools and technologies, including firewalls, antivirus software, and intrusion detection systems

> Ability to work independently and take on complex tasks with little supervision.

> Strong communication and collaboration skills.

> Certified Ethical Hacker (CEH) or similar certification is a plus.

Technical Skills:

Network Security:

Understanding of network protocols and architecture.

Firewalls, Intrusion Detection Systems (IDS), Intrusion Prevention Systems (IPS), Virtual Private Networks (VPNs), and Network Access Control (NAC).

Vulnerability Assessment and Penetration Testing (VAPT):

Knowledge of common vulnerabilities and attack vectors.

Experience with penetration testing tools like Metasploit, Burp Suite, OWASP ZAP, Nessus, etc.

Familiarity with various VAPT methodologies and frameworks.

Application Security:

Understanding of application architecture and development frameworks.

Knowledge of web application security concepts, such as OWASP Top 10 vulnerabilities.

Experience in web application testing using tools like Burp Suite, OWASP ZAP, etc.

Secure coding practices.

API Testing:

Understanding of API protocols (REST, SOAP).

Knowledge of API security vulnerabilities and testing techniques.

Familiarity with tools like Postman, Fiddler, etc., for API testing.

Database Security (SQLi):

Understanding of SQL injection (SQLi) vulnerabilities and prevention techniques.

Knowledge of database management systems (DBMS) and their security configurations.

Tools and Utilities:

Proficiency in tools like Nmap for network scanning and enumeration.

Familiarity with server vulnerability scanning tools like OpenVAS, Nessus, etc.

Understanding of password cracking and brute force tools.

Server and Web Security:

Knowledge of server operating systems (e.g., Linux, Windows) and their security configurations.

Familiarity with web server configurations (e.g., Apache, Nginx) and security best practices.

Data Extraction and Analysis:

Experience with data extraction tools and techniques.

Knowledge of data analysis and visualization tools (e.g., Python, R, Tableau).

Soft Skills:

Communication:

Strong written and verbal communication skills to effectively convey findings and recommendations to stakeholders.

Problem-Solving:

Analytical thinking and problem-solving abilities to identify and mitigate security risks.

Time Management:

Efficiently manage time and prioritize tasks to meet deadlines and project goals.

Continuous Learning:

Stay updated with the latest cybersecurity trends, tools, and techniques through self-study, certifications, and industry conferences.

Teamwork and Collaboration:

Ability to work effectively in a team and collaborate with others in a diverse cybersecurity environment.

Ethical Mindset:

Strong ethics and integrity, understanding the importance of responsible and legal hacking.

Certifications:

Pursuing relevant certifications is highly recommended to validate your skills and knowledge:

Certified Ethical Hacker (CEH)

Offensive Security Certified Professional (OSCP)

Certified Information Systems Security Professional (CISSP)

GIAC Web Application Penetration Tester (GWAPT)

CompTIA Security+

Cisco Certified Network Associate (CCNA)

etc.

Continuous learning, hands-on experience, and staying up-to-date with the rapidly evolving cybersecurity landscape are key to becoming an effective cybersecurity specialist with expertise in VAPT, network security, security audits, application testing, API testing, SQLi, brute force, Nmap, server vulnerabilities,

